{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:23.376528+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here is a summary of how to run, build, and preview this React admin app for different environments.\n\n---\n\n## Project Overview\n\n- **Stack**: Vite 4, React 18, TypeScript, MUI (Material-UI)\n- **Package manager**: Yarn (yarn.lock present, `yarn install`)\n- **Configuration files** are in `envs/` — loaded dynamically by `vite.config.ts` based on the `NODE_ENV` environment variable.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js (LTS recommended)\n- Yarn (`npm install -g yarn`) or npm\n\n---\n\n## 2. Local Development\n\n### Start the dev server (local environment)\n```bash\nyarn dev\n# or: npm run dev\n```\nThis runs `cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host`, loading **`envs/.env.local`**.  \nThe app will be served at **http://localhost:10086** (as defined by `VITE_PORT=10086` in `.env.local`) and available on the network (`--host` flag).\n\n### Start the dev server (staging environment)\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n# or: npm run dev:stg\n```\nLoads **`envs/.env.stg`** instead.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Building for Different Environments\n\nThe project uses Vite build **modes** that correspond to the environment files:\n\n| Command | Vite Mode | Env File Used | Output Dir |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | `prod` | `envs/.env.prod` | `dist` |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `test` | `envs/.env.stg` | `dist` |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `production` | `envs/.env.prod` | `dist` |\n\n**Note**: `yarn build` (default) and `yarn build:prod` both use `.env.prod` — the difference is the `--mode` flag passed to Vite (`prod` vs `production`), which can be used for conditional logic in the codebase.\n\n### Examples\n\n```bash\n# Production build\nyarn build\n\n# Staging build\nyarn build:stg\n\n# Explicit production build\nyarn build:prod\n```\n\nAll builds output to the `dist/` directory (configurable via `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR` in each env file).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Previewing the Built App Locally\n\nAfter building, preview the production bundle with the built-in Vite preview server:\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n# or: npm run serve\n```\nRuns `vite preview --host`, making the contents of `dist/` available on the network.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Docker Build & Deployment\n\nA `Dockerfile` is provided for containerized deployment:\n\n```bash\n# Build the Docker image\ndocker build -t vite-react-admin .\n\n# Run the container (serves on port 80)\ndocker run -p 8080:80 vite-react-admin\n```\n\nThe Dockerfile:\n1. Uses a **multi-stage build** — `node:lts-alpine` to install deps and run `yarn build`\n2. Copies the output (`dist/`) into an **nginx:alpine** image\n3. Applies the custom **`nginx.conf`** (gzip, SPA fallback via `try_files`, and an optional `/admin` sub-path)\n4. Exposes port **80**\n\n---\n\n## 6. Netlify Deployment\n\nThe `netlify.toml` file adds a catch-all redirect for SPA routing:\n\n```toml\n[[redirects]]\n  from = \"/*\"\n  to = \"/\"\n  status = 200\n```\n\nDeploy the `dist/` folder to Netlify (or any static host). All paths fall back to `/index.html`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Environment Variables (`.env` files)\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `NODE_ENV` | Determines which env file is loaded |\n| `VITE_BUILD_ENV` | Environment label (e.g. `development`, `production`) |\n| `VITE_HOST` | Target host domain |\n| `VITE_PORT` | Dev server port |\n| `VITE_BASE_URL` | Base path for assets (`./` for relative) |\n| `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR` | Build output folder name |\n| `VITE_APP_BASE_API` | Base API URL for backend calls |\n\nTo override any variable locally, create a `.env` file in the project root (the config checks for `.env` first before falling back to `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}`).\n\n---\n\n## Quick-Start Summary\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nyarn install\n\n# Copy a local env (optional — the dev script will load envs/.env.local automatically)\ncp envs/.env.local .env\n\n# Start developing\nyarn dev\n\n# Build for production\nyarn build\n\n# Preview the production build\nyarn serve\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1461, "prompt_tokens": 8324, "total_tokens": 9785, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 372, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7936}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7936, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 388}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "d5884f58-f868-4b3e-9cf9-93cb2d9d86c6", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e6-730a-7bf1-ba78-43f6578426cc-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8324, "output_tokens": 1461, "total_tokens": 9785, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7936}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 372}}}}]}}}
